title: Oct. 14 TV Picks: ‘Arrow’ on The CW
text:
‘Arrow’ Billionaire-turned-crusader Oliver Queen (Stephen Amell) continues to keep the streets of Starling City safe in the fourth season of this TV adaptation of the DC Comic. Katie Cassidy, David Ramsey, Willa Holland and Paul Blackthorne are also featured in the cast. 8 p.m. Wednesday, Oct. 14, on The CW.

Doug Knoop: dknoop@seattletimes.com or on Twitter @dougknoop 

Also on Wednesday Most Read Stories Seattle Seahawks release WR B.J. Daniels, RB Rod Smith Ana Mari Cauce new UW president; popular on, off campus USC fires head coach Steve Sarkisian, former UW Huskies coach Seattle council candidate alleges shakedown by developer Truck wrecks cause huge I-5 backups during morning rush Unlimited Digital Access. $1 for 4 weeks. “MLS Soccer,” 6:30 p.m. (ROOT): Portland Timbers at Real Salt Lake (Live).
“The Mysteries of Laura,” 8 p.m. (NBC): Laura and the team join the search for two convicted killers — one being their former captain — who escaped from a maximum-security prison.
“Empire,” 9 p.m. (Fox): Despite their feud, the Lyons decide to collaborate on a project that will benefit both companies; Lucious wants to make Vernon disappear.
“blackish,” 9:31 p.m. (ABC): Dre and his colleagues create a holiday initiative called Daddy’s Day — everything that Father’s Day is not; Junior tries to help Bow around the house.
“Code Black,” 10 p.m. (CBS): During a 36-hour shift, the doctors are faced with a distraught woman whose sons were in a devastating car accident; Mario makes Angus perform an unnecessary operation
